  -- PROOF THAT G(n) < infinity FOR ALL FINITE n (ANANTA)
  --
  -- For finite n, the product has finitely many terms, each > 0.
  -- Therefore product > 0, therefore G = 1/product < infinity.
  --
  -- Ghana is always finite. You never reach infinite density.
  -- Because you never see from all dimensions at once. QED.

  derived "G(n) < infinity for all finite n: ghana is always finite because the number of seen dimensions is finite" from "sangati/aayaama-vistara.om, sangati/ananta.om"

